				\begin{document}$$\:{SNP}_{i}$$\end{document} represented the number of risk alleles [42]. Participants with missing SNPs typing data or demographic data were excluded from this study. In addition, we utilized multivariable logistic regression to estimate the effect size of HCV infection on kidney cancer after adjusting age (Field ID: 21022), sex (Field ID: 31), body mass index (BMI) (Field ID: 21001), smoking (Field ID: 20116), alcohol intake frequency (Field ID: 1558), race (Field ID: 21000) using R software (v4.1.3). Considering that individuals from different ancestral backgrounds have systematic frequency differences across SNP loci that are associated with disease risk or exposure factors, UK Biobank calculated principal components to control population stratification, which increased the credibility of causal inference [43]. According to previous literature, the tops 10 principal components (Field ID: 22009) was also included in adjustive variable [41]. P < 0.05 was considered statistically significant.
